Con- sult note on Epode ii. 50.-43. Rapum. The rape is a plant of the genus Brassica, called also cole-rape and cole-seed, and of which the navew, or French turnip, is a variety.—44. Inulas. The elecampane marks a genus of plants of many species The common elecampane has a perennial, thick, branching root, of a strong odour, and is used in medicine.
